We recommended the following:
The Local Chief Executive (LCE) and concerned municipal officials to formulate written policies or guidelines on the grant of financial assistance or donations, containing the type of assistance, qualification of beneficiaries and the amount allowable, and the documentary requirements;
The LCE to direct the MSWDO to ensure that all individuals/beneficiaries given assistance be referred for eligibility evaluation/assessment and a case study report be prepared and  form part of the supporting documents of the claim;
The LCE to direct the Municipal Accountant and Acting Municipal Treasurer to support the claims with appropriate and complete documentation pursuant to Section 4(6) of P.D. No. 1445; and
The LCE and concerned municipal officials to strictly observe the pertinent provisions of PD No. 1445 and RA No. 7160 on the proper disposition of government funds pertaining to financial assistance/donations.

Fund Transfers received from the Iloilo Provincial Government remained unliquidated as of December 31, 2017, thereby exposing the Municipality to potential risk of non-compliance with the Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) that may result to deferment of additional grant of fund transfers which could deprive the constituents of the benefits that may be derived from the intended projects to help them elevate their social, economic and environmental conditions.

We recommended that the LCE direct:

a. The Municipal Accountant and Acting Municipal Treasurer to monitor the receipts and corresponding disbursements of funds, ensure the completeness of the liquidation reports and supporting documents, in accordance with Section 3.1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-001, and submit the same to the IPG and IA Audit Team, if such projects are already implemented;

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the following:
The Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory of the Municipality’s properties; and likewise to require department/office heads to submit lists of properties existing in their respective offices to the Committee for validation and consolidation;
The Inventory Committee to prepare the inventory report and submit to the OIC-Municipal Accountant and Designated GSO for reconciliation, and to the Office of the Auditor within the prescribed period;
The Designated GSO and OIC-Municipal Accountant to prepare, maintain and update the property cards and PPE ledger cards for easy monitoring, proper identification and validation of properties;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant and Designated GSO to reconcile their records and make appropriate adjustments if any,  to present accurate and reliable PPE balances in the financial statements; and
The Designated GSO to issue ARE to Municipal officials and employees concerned to cover the equipment issued for proper control and accountability of equipment.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the following:
The OIC-Municipal Accountant to analyze, reconcile and identify/trace the details of transactions debited or credited to Loans Payable Account and prepare the adjusting entries to correct and present the appropriate balances in the financial statements;
The Acting Municipal Treasurer to request from the LBP - Iloilo Lending Center and DBP - Jaro Branch the appropriate supporting documents/records pertaining to the Municipality’s existing loans, and furnish copies to the Office of the Municipal Accountant for them to verify and reconcile the differences/ variances in the loan balances, and effect the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts, if any, to conform with the amounts provided by the Banks, and to present the correct amount of the Loans Payable;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant to reclassify the current portions of the loans payable to the current liability in order to present properly the current and non-current liabilities in accordance with PPSAS I; and
The Acting Municipal Treasurer to fully comply with the provisions and terms of the contract to avoid payment of unnecessary expenses for penalties and surcharges.

Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
The Local Chief Executive (LCE) to direct the concerned Municipal officials and employees to liquidate and/or refund immediately their unused cash advances pursuant to the provisions of Section 89 of PD No. 1445, and COA Circular Nos. 97-002 and 96-004, to avoid accumulation of unliquidated cash advances and to attain a fair presentation of the relevant accounts in the financial statements;
The LCE to direct the imposition of appropriate sanctions for the unjustified failure of the concerned Municipal officials and employees to liquidate their cash advances;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records relative to the grant, utilization and liquidation of cash advances and prepare necessary adjusting entries to correct the balances;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant to only acknowledge and record liquidation of cash advances upon presentation of sufficient and appropriate documents evidencing payment of expenses equivalent to the amount granted. If the money advanced is not fully utilized, require refund of the unspent amount evidenced by an Official Receipt before recording the settlement; and
The Accountable Officers to use the cash advance solely for the specific legal purpose for which it was granted and not incur expenses in excess of the authorized amount granted.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the concerned officials and employees to:
Set-up and maintain a Gender and Development (GAD) Database that will serve as basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation; and, formulate GAD Codes or Ordinances that will support the LGU’s efforts in promoting, protecting and fulfilling women’s human rights, economic empowerment and gender-responsive governance towards the attainment of gender equality and women’s empowerment;
Allocate at least five percent (5%) of their annual budget appropriations to support GAD Programs/Projects/Activities (PPAs);
Ensure submission of the Annual GAD Plan and Budget  and GAD Accomplishment Report  in required format together with necessary documents to the DILG Regional Office VI for review and approval to ascertain compliance with the guidelines;
Ensure the full utilization of the allocated budget and propose plans/ programs for GAD to maximize the funds and benefits thereof and ensure that the relevant LGU PPAs and GAD activities will address/respond to the gender issues identified; and
Strictly adhere to the provisions of JMC No. 2013-01 of the PCW, DILG, DBM and NEDA.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the LCE direct the following:
The Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory of the Municipality’s properties;
Involve each office/unit of the Municipality to conduct respective inventory taking and tagging using stickers with control numbers and record all PPE existing in the offices and same shall be validated by the Inventory Committee;
Consolidate all validated inventory reports from the respective offices, together with the corresponding  property numbers, which shall be used as basis for the preparation of the PPE ledger cards and Inventory Report to be submitted by the Inventory Committee to the Auditor, Municipal Accountant and GSO for proper identification of all PPE;
The Accounting and General Services Offices to reconcile their records and any discrepancies be adjusted to properly present accurate and reliable PPE balances in the financial statements; and
Prepare an updated ARE, with corresponding serial numbers, to be issued to concerned accountable officers/property holders.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the LCE direct the following:
The OIC-Municipal Accountant to prepare the BRS for SEF and all TF accounts and submit to the Auditor monthly pursuant to COA Circular No. 96-011;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant and OIC-Municipal Treasurer to request from the LBP-Sara Branch for copies of supporting documents relative to the reconciling items presented in the BRS;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant and OIC-Municipal Treasurer to ensure coordination between their offices for timely submission of all the necessary documents to facilitate the proper and timely preparation of the BRS that will support the Cash in Bank balances;
The OIC-Municipal Accountant, upon receipt of necessary documents, to  update the BRS and draw journal entry vouchers for the corrections and/or adjustments to ensure the accuracy and reliability of balances presented in the Financial Statements; and
The OIC-Municipal Treasurer to submit a request to LBP - Sara Branch to close the dormant accounts, ECCD and Lead for Health Project, and transfer the  balances to the Municipality’s TF account; while the MDRRMC account shall be maintained for the LDRRMF.
We also recommended that the LCE provide additional staff to the OIC-Municipal Accountant to assist in the preparation of various financial reports.

We recommended that the LCE direct the concerned officials and employees in-charge/assigned in the implementation of the SWM Program in the Municipality to adhere strictly to the provisions of RA No. 9003.
We also recommended the following:
Require the strict implementation of  waste segregation at source;
Implement separate collection schedules for specific types of wastes, and ensure that such shall cover all the barangays in the Municipality;
Observe the use of separate compartment/container with cover for specific types of wastes to ensure the containment of solid wastes while in transit;
Coordinate with Barangay Officials regarding information dissemination/ campaign on proper segregation and disposal of wastes to be implemented in their barangay; and
Impose strictly the collection of garbage fees and penalties as provided in the Municipal Ordinance.
